      "updated": 1784125503230,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "To solve this i imported the ArrayList and Comparator classes\nand then made a custom object called Pair and made it contain out key and value\nas its attributes, then i iterated through the given input to push any such new pair \ninto the arraylist called Pairs. i designed functions that checked if an object with a given key\nalready existed, if yes then increased the value attribute. otherwise initialised a new pair object and \nadded it to the arraylist. This way i got an arraylist of pair. then i wanted to sort these by their\nvalues in ascending order. For this java has a Comparator class so i used to make a comparator object\nand then i overide the int public compare method to return Integer.compare() based on the value.\nThen to find the top k elements i made a k sized array to store the keys corresponding to the max values\nand then returned the keys array completing the problem. code is at our repo.",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "To solve this i imported the ArrayList and Comparator classes\nand then made a custom object called Pair and made it contain out key and value\nas its attributes, then i iterated through the given input to push any such new pair \ninto the arraylist called Pairs. i designed functions that checked if an object with a given key\nalready existed, if yes then increased the value attribute. otherwise initialised a new pair object and \nadded it to the arraylist. This way i got an arraylist of pair. then i wanted to sort these by their\nvalues in ascending order. For this java has a Comparator class so i used to make a comparator object\nand then i overide the int public compare method to return Integer.compare() based on the value.\nThen to find the top k elements i made a k sized array to store the keys corresponding to the max values\nand then returned the keys array completing the problem. code is at our repo.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
